nd Labor in the United States provides a comprehensive and detailed understanding of labor relations in American sports for scholars, those interested in labor issues, and sports fans.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCollective bargainingxSportsxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aCollective bargainingxSportszUnited States. 0aProfessional athletesxLabor unionsxUnited States. 0aProfessional athletesxLabor unionszUnited States. 0aProfessional sports contractsxUnited States. 0aProfessional sports contractszUnited States. 0aProfessional sportsxEconomic aspectsxUnited States. 0aProfessional sportsxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aProfessional sportsxLaw and legislationxUnited States. 0aProfessional sportsxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 4aHistory : American Labor History. 4aSociology : Sociology of Work. 4aSociology : Sports and Society. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Sociology of Sports.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438456836?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438456836423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438456836/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles